cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.LT, cs.FL, cs.SE 

This paper deals with topics related to logic and type theory, specifically the use of a necessity-like modality in a typed $\lambda$-calculus. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). The paper also discusses recursion and reflection, which are topics commonly studied in programming languages and compilers, suggesting that cs.PL (Programming Languages) and cs.SE (Software Engineering) are also likely sub-categories. The paper also touches on formal languages and automata, which are topics covered in cs.LT (Automata and Formal Languages) and cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory).
